##Civilian Volunteers, is how to implement the first-line materials

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Paper reporter, Li Siwen, intern, Xue Xiaodong

On February 13, the pro-orange Xiaogan team, a group of volunteer volunteers, also implemented 100 protective suits to be donated, 50,000 N95 masks, 2.6 tons of rice, 5 tons of alcohol and 14 oxygen inhalers that cost 100,000 yuan each, ready for transport to the front line.

The team, assembled on New Year's Eve, raised more than 700 boxes of medical disinfectant and 5,000 N95 masks on the first day of the Lunar New Year. Within a week, sent to Xiaogan more than 100 tons of disinfectant, more than 200,000 pairs of gloves, more than 100,000 masks, more than 20,000 pieces of surgical protective clothing, thousands of PCS protective clothing and goggles.

"We spell focus, we spell speed. Not More, more! " Said Maodanhong, one of the core organizers of the volunteer team, in order to ensure efficient operation, the team divided 150 volunteers into groups according to fund, purchase, logistics, official letter, receipt and so on, treat each material with a "project-oriented" thinking.

5,000 masks to be handed out on New Year's Eve

On the eve of the New Year on January 24, Xiaogan Renzi Yu, who works for Alibaba in Hangzhou, received a phone call from his old classmate Wen Sheng. "Our hometown is in short supply. Can you get some protective equipment? " A simple phone call, let Word Jade realize the home filial piety situation has been critical.

Wen Sheng, a delegate to the Hubei Provincial People's Congress and a professor at the Hubei Institute of Engineering, told The Paper news that on the second day of the city's closure, a large amount of supplies and hospitals were pouring into Wuhan, but the high-risk cities around Wuhan face a "dark under the lights" situation. "At that time, there were not many cases reported in Xiaogan, but the number of confirmed cases was increasing all over Hubei Province. Once the number of Xiaogan infections surged, ordinary citizens and health care workers were exposed to high risks. "

Wen Sheng had planned to find colleagues in the chemical plant to raise disinfection water, but the manufacturers and enterprises he knew during the Spring Festival have been on holiday, which has deepened his concerns. In order to find more materials, Wen Sheng asked almost all the known colleagues and friends, word jade is one of them.

At that time the word jade work group just in the New Year Red Envelope, hang up the phone, he also followed a red envelope, the caption is: Hubei Xiaogan serious epidemic, URGENT MEDICAL EPIDEMIC MATERIALS! There are local officials to meet, can be directly connected to the first line!

"At the beginning, I just wanted to send a red envelope to see who had the materials to connect with, but I didn't expect to gather 30 or 40 volunteers that night. " Zi Yu said that after sending the message, a dozen colleagues immediately sent private messages asking questions, most of them are from Hubei Province.

One of the most active response, she took the lead in establishing a volunteer group, began to form a volunteer team. She recalls, "I sent out a message asking for help. A Restaurant Entrepreneur saw my message in the early hours of the morning and immediately contacted a water disinfector to secure the first donations. When the two deterministic materials to docking, I put the demand side together, Xiaoganwen teachers also added the group, our volunteer work has thus started."

Within 24 hours, in the word jade and Maodanhong organization, quickly formed a cross-business departments, completely spontaneous "pro-orange Xiaogan" civil volunteer team.

On the first day of the Lunar New Year, the team of 30 to 40 volunteers has raised more than 700 boxes of medical disinfectant and 5,000 N95 masks. Two days later, 60 tons of hydrogen peroxide donated by Jinhe, Anhui Province, arrived at the Xiaonan district epidemic headquarters in Xiaogan city. In just one week, more than 100 tons of disinfectant, more than 200,000 pairs of gloves, more than 100,000 masks, more than 20,000 surgical protective clothing, thousands of PCS protective clothing and goggles reached the front line of Xiaogan.

"The first batch of disinfection water that arrived on the 27th was immediately used in the Xiaogan Prevention and Control Command Center, Police Affairs, Sentry Posts and other front lines, " Wen said. The disinfection water helped the front line for more than 10 days and solved the immediate problem.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"Good News" is coming out every day from within the material group. All images in this article are provided by the interviewees

Sub-group monitoring materials, "project-based" operation

How does a huge supply chain work? In this team, the volunteers with the core of the word Jade, Maodanhong are responsible for the preparation, management, transportation of materials, in Hubei Wensheng is responsible for the local material docking. Word Jade said, the volunteer team is divided into funds, procurement, logistics, letters, receipt and other groups, "we take the material clues as a project to track and manage. ".

"If there is a material clue, we will pull a small group, and then there will be a volunteer in the group who will keep an eye on the material and track the delivery and logistics, " Zi said, but what is the status of the business point below, are uncertain, each need volunteers to track, if there is a problem quickly coordination.

But in the process of implementation, they have encountered unimaginable obstacles. Maodanhong said that the accuracy of material screening, the timeliness of the purchase of funds, the smooth flow of logistics, are civilian volunteer teams in the aid epidemic areas often face difficulties.

In the process of raising funds, the first difficulty is to "find money. ".

"The vendors didn't accept the first delivery of several supplies we received on the 26th, and the goods were snatched in a split second due to a time difference, " said Maodanhong, who said that when the team was first set up, they had already missed out on several supplies due to lack of funds.

At that time, dozens of volunteers immediately made voluntary donations, raising about 100,000 yuan of Public Welfare Fund, but in the face of huge material consumption, 100,000 yuan is just a drop in the bucket.

"We don't have enough money to buy so many supplies, so we have to look for them everywhere, " Zi said. In order to solve the funding problem, the "pro-orange Xiaogan" team set up a fund group to coordinate with the foundation, he soon joined forces with the Huazhong University of Science and Technology, the Beijing New Sunshine Charity Fund, the Amity Foundation and more than 20 other social care organizations and enterprises.

The Fund's volunteers identify the requirements of some funds, the funds raised to the procurement team to buy masks, disinfectant, protective clothing and other scarce materials. Materials in place, and then by the logistics group one by one call different express, logistics company's phone, asked whether the delivery, when can be delivered. Due to the tight control of traffic, volunteers are also required to set aside special groups to carry out official government letters and send receipts to charity organizations and enterprises after receiving supplies in the affected areas.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Supplies raised by the "pro-orange Xiaogan" team

While most of the volunteers were not on the ground, Maodanhong said, the core members of the team worked around the clock almost 10 hours a day to connect with sources of supply, funds, logistics and local governments. "I basically keep my phone in my hand because I type faster, and after three or four days my pinkie gets cramped and I can only speak. But there are always some typos in the translation, and then when the fingers get better, they start typing again."

By the end of the day, the volunteer group had a more nuanced division of Labor: Different volunteers followed different supplies, and when the group reached 130, the group turned on the invitation process to keep the team in control, improve the efficiency and accuracy of screening material qualification.

As of February 13, there were 150 people in the volunteer group. The volunteers come from all over the country, and even from Vietnam. They note in the group that "volunteer No. 1, Volunteer No. 2... " Many people do not know each other, but he became his closest teammate by helping Xiaogan.

Express delivery logistics difficult, because the cost of high abandoned helicopters

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Collected on February 13, it is being checked for packaging and ready to be sent to the anti-epidemic line.

In the case of "closed city" in Wuhan and traffic jam in many places, the transportation problem has become the biggest problem.

After learning that a caring Vietnamese man with five boxes of face masks had been stuck at the customs office, Wen Sheng rushed to the command center to apply for a donation letter and ask the Vietnamese customs to let him go, Mao said. But after the people in love arrived in Guangxi, in Guangxi customs contact a number of express companies have not been able to send goods directly to Hubei, taxi to the city center is also facing the same problem. Finally, the volunteers discussed a circuitous mailing method, first materials sent to Guangzhou, and then by Guangzhou Volunteers Contact Express Company, will send 5 boxes of masks to Xiaogan.

"The epidemic has caught up with the Chinese New Year, " Zi told The Paper news. "The logistics situation is complicated. For example, in Shunfeng, some places can be sent, some places can't be sent. Sometimes Debon says they can, but when he calls, he says they can't. We have to check every batch one by one, not only to make sure the goods are sent, but also to make sure that the stations are in normal condition during the transportation. "

In order to ensure that the materials reach the epidemic area as soon as possible, in addition to logistics and express delivery, the team sometimes has to coordinate with the aviation department, "If some supplies need to be transferred, they have to fly to the Hemerocallis Fulva airport in Changsha, and then from the Hemerocallis Fulva airport to send them to the affected areas, " Zi said, adding that on one occasion the team also communicated by helicopter to transport medical alcohol, it was later found to be too expensive and was converted to a tanker.

Meng Bai, a volunteer from Ali's rookie department, said that everyone was "crossing the river by feeling for stones" during the whole process, "At the beginning, we didn't have enough experience. When we got dozens of cases of disinfectant, we were anxious to deliver the goods. But in fact, we couldn't deliver the goods in time even if the goods were scattered and the cargo was small. " Meng Bai said that scattered goods would all be gathered in one place as far as possible during subsequent shipments, coordinate the delivery.

"For example, once we sent the goods to Xiaogan, the car was found, but the goods were not enough, so we had to continue to contact the foundation and the manufacturer to seize the goods, to make up 17.1 tons, and finally the overnight delivery truck was delivered to the Xiaogan Command Center at 7:40 pm on the fourth day of the eighth Lunar Month, " said Meng Bai, in the process, my role changed from charity donor to logistics, then to sourcing, then to procurement broker, and finally to the whole chain of service scheduling command.

But there was one aspect of the whole process that was particularly moving to the volunteers. Mao Danhong said that on January 29, volunteers had arranged for supplies and vehicles to go to Wuhan to transport 900 boxes of 84 sterile water, "A police station in Wuhan bought 20 cases through us, and while they came to take the 20 cases of disinfectant, they also sent a car to help us distribute the rest of the disinfectant to various hospitals. We were quite moved. "

Although each batch of supplies had to be coordinated by various parties, the supplies of the "pro-orange Xiaogan" volunteer team were eventually received to Hubei, Chongqing, Fujian, Zhejiang and other provinces, and played a major role in the first-line fight against the epidemic.

"There are still a lot of people who have come to us, whether it is the demand side, the supply side or the foundation, and they have asked us to help coordinate, " she said. Most of our volunteers have already returned to work, using their evening time in the landing of these work. So I hope people in the community will pay more attention and support Hubei."
